<i>noun</i>: 호령 [호ː령 ], 핀잔 [핀잔], 잔소리 [잔소리], 야단 [야ː단], 닦달 [닥딸], 나무람 [나무람], 꾸지람 [꾸지람], 꾸중 [꾸중], 걱정 [걱쩡] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>호령 [호ː령 ]</dt><br>
<dd>1. command; order</dd><br>
<dd>부하나 동물을 지휘하여 명령함. 또는 그 명령.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of giving a command to lead one's subordinate or animal; or such a command.</dd><br>
<dd>2. scolding; stern rebuke; roar</dd><br>
<dd>큰 소리로 꾸짖음.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of scolding another in a loud voice.</dd><br>
<dd>3. command; order</dd><br>
<dd>여러 사람이 일정한 동작을 함께 취하도록 하기 위해 지휘자가 말로 내리는 간단한 명령.</dd><br>
<dd>A simple command shouted out for people to do the same movements together.</dd><br>
<dt>핀잔 [핀잔]</dt><br>
<dd>telling-off; scolding; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>못마땅하게 여겨 꾸짖는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of scolding someone due to one's discontent with him/her.</dd><br>
<dt>잔소리 [잔소리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. useless talk; idle talk</dd><br>
<dd>쓸데없이 자질구레한 말을 늘어놓음. 또는 그 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of talking about trifling matters uselessly; such talk.</dd><br>
<dd>2. nitpicking; preaching; scolding</dd><br>
<dd>필요 이상으로 듣기 싫은 말을 하며 꾸짖거나 참견함. 또는 그런 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of rebuking someone or interfering in his/her affair while saying unnecessary things that he/she does not want to hear; such words.</dd><br>
<dt>야단 [야ː단]</dt><br>
<dd>1. uproar; tumult; clamor</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일 때문에 시끄럽게 자꾸 떠들거나 소란을 일으킴.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making a noise or making a row due to something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. scolding; chiding; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람의 잘못을 큰소리로 혼냄.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of criticizing someone's mistake in a loud voice.</dd><br>
<dd>3. trouble; predicament; quandary</dd><br>
<dd>매우 곤란한 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A very awkward situation.</dd><br>
<dt>닦달 [닥딸]</dt><br>
<dd>scolding; rebuking</dd><br>
<dd>끈질기게 잔소리를 하거나 윽박지르고 혼을 냄.</dd><br>
<dd>Nagging continuously, or scolding and bullying.</dd><br>
<dt>나무람 [나무람]</dt><br>
<dd>scolding; reproach; blaming</dd><br>
<dd>잘못을 꾸짖어 잘 알아듣게 말하는 것. 또는 잘못을 꾸짖어 잘 알아듣게 해 주는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of pointing out the fault of someone and advising the person on how to behave better next time, or the remark itself.</dd><br>
<dt>꾸지람 [꾸지람]</dt><br>
<dd>scolding; admonition</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 꾸짖는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of an elder pointing out a mistake or wrongdoing of a younger person.</dd><br>
<dt>꾸중 [꾸중]</dt><br>
<dd>scolding; admonition</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람의 잘못을 꾸짖음.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of an elder pointing out a mistake or wrongdoing of a younger person.</dd><br>
<dt>걱정 [걱쩡]</dt><br>
<dd>1. worry; concern; care</dd><br>
<dd>좋지 않은 일이 있을까 봐 두렵고 불안함.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of feeling afraid and uneasy, in fear of the possible occurrence of something bad.</dd><br>
<dd>2. scolding; blaming</dd><br>
<dd>아랫사람의 잘못을 꾸짖음.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of scolding a younger person for his/her fault.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>